title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1980-08-30
lineage: AUD @ Soundboard w/Senn 421's mounted on a pole> Sony TC-D5> CM > Nak Dragon >Sony PCM R-700 > D > HD > SndFge > CDR
description: Feel Like A Stranger, Peggy-O, Cassidy, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Cold Rain & Snow-> Looks Like Rain, Easy To Love You, Althea, Jack Straw Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, CC Rider-> Ramble On Rose, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Hot Spectrum Show I have been looking for this show for awhile.  Unfortunately this sound quality does not do it justice.  (my star rating reflects only that).  Rocking, high energy performance.  Hear Jerry's playing on Jack Straw.  "... jack straw from wichita cut his buddy down ...".  Gives me a shiver.

Jack Straw indeed! I know 1980 isn't exactly the first year that comes to mind when one thinks of powerhouse Jack Straws, but this one is a real sledgehammer! Check it out, then seek out the soundboard or a better audience elsewhere.

Not This Recording I was at this show.  It was hot, especially the first set.  But don't bother with this recording.  I'm surprised that the folks with the archive didn't quality control this one better because there are better recordings of this show out there.  How do I know?  I've got one.  I've tried to submit it to the Archive, but they don't let just anyone join their club.

Hey Marty, Could We Trade? Sorry to hear you haven't been able to upload the show.  I'm an old Head who likes trading.  Love to do some business with you if you're up to it.  I've got some great stuff that's been taken off the site.   Thanks.  jacknds@cs.com.
